HEADWORD: Timeserver
<hw>Time"serv`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who adapts
his opinions and manners to the times; one who obsequiously compiles
with the ruling power; -- now used only in a bad sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

